taylor chain i & ii are a pair of documentary films , produced by kartemquin films , that first examine a &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; workers ' strike at a hammond , indiana , chain manufacturing plant and then follow the collective &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; process of the same plant one decade later . originally released by kartemquin as two separate short documentaries in 1980 and 1984 , taylor chain i & ii were released together to show how the decade-long labor movement was affected by the recession and &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; legislation of the early 1980s . taylor chain i : the story in a union local begins in the 1970s , as workers at the taylor chain manufacturing plant begin negotiations with management for a new contract . cameras go from the factory floor into the union hall , as workers both young and old argue about &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; within proposed contracts . the negotiations lead to a &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; strike , as the union takes to the &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; line . eventually , both sides make &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; and the workers return to work . taylor chain ii : the story of collective &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; begins ten years later , in the early 1980s , as both workers and management are attempting to save the plant as recession and globalization have reduced the factory 's workforce drastically . the union and management sit across from one another in a holiday inn conference room , trying to come to a compromise that will both save the plant as well as take care of the workforce . in the end , the two sides come to an agreement , but it is not enough to save taylor chain from closure . directed by jerry &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; and gordon quinn , taylor chain i was the winner of the 1980 william friedkin award at the chicago international film festival . also directed by &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; and quinn , taylor chain ii won the first award at the 1985 international labor communications association film & broadcast competition . broadcast on public television , taylor chain